The paper also involves the use of probability measures and divergences, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses the problem of guessing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with error exponent bounds, which is a topic in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
